cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SpaceLLM: a Python framework for radiation-tolerant transformer training and inference in space"
message: "If you use SpaceLLM in research, please cite it using the metadata in this file."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Uckan"
    given-names: "Arda Can"
    email: "ardacan.uckan@healcapital.com"
    affiliation: "Independent"
repository-code: "https://github.com/ardacanuckan/spacellm"
url: "https://github.com/ardacanuckan/spacellm"
abstract: >-
  SpaceLLM is a Python framework for protecting transformer model
  parameters, optimizer state, and KV-caches against single-event
  upsets in space-radiation environments. It composes a calibrated
  Weibull/IRPP physics environment with HuggingFace-compatible
  protection strategies (selective TMR, attention checksum,
  KV-cache parity, layer-norm and embedding fingerprints) and a
  bench harness that reports silent-error rate and overhead. The
  shipped device profiles are validated against publicly fetched
  primary-source beam-test data within an explicit ECSS-style
  envelope.
keywords:
  - radiation tolerance
  - transformers
  - large language models
  - on-orbit computing
  - single-event upset
  - SEU
  - fault injection
  - PyTorch
  - HuggingFace
